  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "A subsequent revision of Rohdes' \"4 P's of Creativity\" was proposed by Jordanous (2016) to include the dimensions of computational creativity in the model.",
    "In this scenario, the \"Person\" was reimagined as the \"Producer,\" which included the software, robot, or computational agent, its developer, and the one who interacts with the tools for creative purposes.",
    "The \"Process\" was extended to the computational dimension, conveying within it the algorithmic processing and the human-machine and machine-environment interactions that lead to creative productions.",
    "The \"Product,\" in the context of computational creativity, is often read as evidence of the machine's creativity, thus risking obscuring the importance of the other \"P's\" that contribute equally to the creative process.",
    "The \"Press\" manifested in this context acts in two directions."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "A subsequent revision of Rohdes' \"4 P's of Creativity\" was proposed by Jordanous (2016) to include the dimensions of computational creativity in the model."
  ]
